1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,251
We spent the next two hours not talking about the merits of different kinds of jobs,

2
00:00:01,281 --> 00:00:04,050
but rather discussing how to set goals.

3
00:00:04,401 --> 00:00:09,170
FB learned, I believe, the most important lesson in career planning.

4
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:12,771
Before you start out, know where you want to go.

5
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:17,410
Like the progressive corporation, plan ahead.

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,371
You are, in a sense, a business unit.

7
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:24,050
Your talents, skills, and abilities are your products.

8
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:28,930
You want to develop your products so they command the highest possible price.

9
00:00:29,201 --> 00:00:31,251
Forward planning will do it.

10
00:00:31,761 --> 00:00:34,050
Here are two steps that will help.

11
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:41,011
First, visualize your future in terms of three departments, work, home, and social.

12
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:48,850
Dividing your life this way keeps you from becoming confused, prevents conflicts, helps you look at the whole picture.

13
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:54,531
Second, demand of yourself clear, precise answers to these questions.

14
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:57,651
What do I want to accomplish with my life?

15
00:00:57,761 --> 00:00:59,331
What do I want to be?

16
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,290
And what does it take to satisfy me?

17
00:01:03,201 --> 00:01:05,811
Using this planning guide will help.

18
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:09,651
An image of me ten years from now.

19
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,651
Ten Years Planning Guide.

20
00:01:12,961 --> 00:01:15,011
A. Work Department.

21
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,371
Ten years from now.

22
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,170
1.

23
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:20,050
What income level do I want to attain?

24
00:01:20,050 --> 00:01:20,850
2.

25
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,971
What level of responsibility do I seek?

26
00:01:23,971 --> 00:01:24,931
3.

27
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:27,730
How much authority do I want to command?

28
00:01:28,081 --> 00:01:28,691
4.

29
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:32,371
What prestige do I expect to gain from my work?

30
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:36,691
B, home department, 10 years from now.

31
00:01:36,961 --> 00:01:42,771
One, what kind of standard of living do I want to provide for my family and myself?

32
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:46,211
Two, what kind of house do I want to live in?

33
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:50,131
Three, what kind of vacations do I want to take?

34
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:56,451
Four, what financial support do I want to give my children in their early adult years?

35
00:01:57,281 --> 00:02:00,771
C, social department, 10 years from now.

36
00:02:00,771 --> 00:02:02,290
1.

37
00:02:02,401 --> 00:02:04,850
What kinds of friends do I want to have?

38
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:05,651
2.

39
00:02:05,841 --> 00:02:08,371
What social groups do I want to join?

40
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,251
3.

41
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:12,931
What community leadership positions would I like to hold?

42
00:02:12,931 --> 00:02:13,811
4.

43
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,490
What worthwhile causes do I want to champion?

44
00:02:18,881 --> 00:02:24,931
A few years ago, my young son insisted the two of us build a doghouse for Peanut,

45
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:30,050
an intelligent pup of dubious pedigree and my son's pride and joy.

46
00:02:30,321 --> 00:02:36,931
His persistence and enthusiasm won, so we proceeded to build a home Peanut could call her own.
